headline: Dr. Oz’s CMS Nomination Sparks Mixed Reaction From Healthcare Investors
summary: The prospect of Dr. Mehmet Oz atop the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services sparked enthusiasm among managed-care investors, sending up shares of UnitedHealth and Humana Wednesday.  Hospital investors were on the opposite side, pushing down the stocks of HCA and Tenet.  The TV personality has been a cheerleader for private Medicare plans in the past, fueling a rise among companies that focus on those products.

headline: UnitedHealth, Cigna, CVS sue FTC over insulin litigation process
summary: The three companies are claiming the FTC’s suit is unconstitutional because it was lodged in the agency’s administrative court, instead of a federal one.
